Women candidates in Embu county have complained over bullying on social media and physical harassment by their rivals, especially in rallies.Susan Nyagah (pictured) is vying for the woman representative seat on a Kanu ticket. She said they are harassed simply because they are women. Nyagah, a contractor, said they find it hard to campaign because they are afraid of the attacks.She spoke when the IEBC met candidates from the county on Tuesday to brief them before the elections. Nyagah urged the IEBC to ensure women aspirants are protected and those aspirants or their agents using social media to attack them along gender lines and using obnoxious remarks are punished. Nyagah urged the IEBC to ensure the women aspirants are protected.Aspirants or their agents using social media to attack women along gender lines and make insulting remarks should be punished, she added.